==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rose-cut
<hw>Rose"-cut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Cut flat on the
reverse, and with a convex face formed of triangular facets in rows; --
said of diamonds and other precious stones. See <cref>Rose
diamond</cref>, under <er>Rose</er>. Cf. <er>Brilliant</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rosedrop</ent>⟦br⟧
